article.headline: Cal Poly 37, Portland St. 25
article.story: SAN LUIS OBISPO, Calif. -- Andre Broadus threw a touchdown pass and ran for a score in the fourth quarter, helping Cal Poly remain unbeaten with a 37-25 victory over Portland State on Saturday night. Portland State (2-5, 1/3 Big Sky) had a 25-23 lead at the close of the third quarter. Broadus threw an 11-yard scoring pass to Willie Tucker with 10:35 left in the game, and Broadus scored on a 1-yard run with 5:39 left. Bobby Zalud gave Cal Poly (7-0, 5-0) a 20-17 lead on a 41-yard field goal with 11:20 left in the third quarter, and Portland State bounced back for a 25-20 lead with 9:04 left in the third. Zalud connected on a 20-yard chip shot field goal with 4:01 showing to bring Cal Poly closer. Broadus finished with two TD passes and two rushing TDs. Cal Poly's Deonte Williams rushed for 169 yards on 27 carries.
